Bug.WithStack:
The CommandLine args tag needs to be modified for the launchProcess (the 
filein context is LaunchProcessCommand) and the change is in startProcCommand.
The change should also address multiple commandline args to be passed.
if(this.getParameter() != null)
		{
			sbuf.append(cmdLnArgsBeginTag);
			sbuf.append(" position=\"append\"" + " 
value=\""+this.getParameter()+"\">");
			sbuf.append(cmdLnArgsCloseTag);
		}
There is no CommandLineArgs tag anymore in the new AC's XML command set.  We replaced the individual tags that made up the set of info to use in launching an application with a single tag "Application" with attributes and sub-elements. The sub-elements are Variable and Parameter.  The Parameter element is where command line arguments are specified, and that element has the notion of replace|prepend|append.  The Variable subelement defines environment variable settings.

Need clarification on what the problem is that caused this defect to be entered.
Was fixed in the Exec framework
As of TPTP 4.6.0, TPTP is in maintenance mode and focusing on improving quality by resolving relevant enhancements/defects and increasing test coverage through test creation, automation, Build Verification Tests (BVTs), and expanded run-time execution. As part of the TPTP Bugzilla housecleaning process (see http://wiki.eclipse.org/Bugzilla_Housecleaning_Processes), this enhancement/defect is verified/closed by the Project Lead since this enhancement/defect has been resolved and unverified for more than 1 year and considered to be fixed. If this enhancement/defect is still unresolved and reproducible in the latest TPTP release (http://www.eclipse.org/tptp/home/downloads/), please re-open.

